other_tests.findings: The appendix is dilated to 15mm with a large amount of fat stranding and small free fluid in the right paracolic gutter. An 8-mm hyperdensity at the appendiceal orifice is an appendicolith. No drainable fluid collection. Mildly distended fluid filled loops of small bowel may be a reactive ileus. The large bowel is normal. No obstruction.
